caption.body: We are very pleased to announce that the Aviation Museum and Library will be open daily starting tomorrow as we are adding Saturday hours. We will now be open daily from 10 am to 4:30pm. “China Clipper”, “Catch Our Style: California Regional Airlines 1950s-1980s”, “Queen of the Skies: The Legacy of the Lockheed Constellation”, “United States Coast Guard Air Station San Francisco Honoring the Guardians of the Golden Gate 75th”, and “Early Birds: Selections from the Tony Bill Aviation Library Collection, 1893–1914”, are currently on display in the Aviation Museum and Library in the International Terminal. See more on our website: http://bit.ly/SFOMuseum
